cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.Distributed, cs.PF, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with a parallel algorithm for solving a minimum spanning tree problem on supercomputers with distributed memory. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithm for solving a minimum spanning tree problem, which falls under the scope of this category. 
3. cs.Distributed - The paper deals with a distributed algorithm for solving a minimum spanning tree problem, which falls under the scope of this category. 
4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper discusses optimization techniques such as hashing and message compression, which are aimed at improving the performance of the algorithm. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with a system (supercomputer) and presents an algorithm for controlling the system to solve a specific problem.
